---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Dataset Licence — Fractune">
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo"><img src="/logo.png" alt="" class="nav-logo-icon" />Fractune</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <h1>Dataset Licence</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Version 1.0 — April 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Scope</h2>
      <p>
        This licence covers all analysis data contributed to and available through the
        Fractune public dataset, including but not limited to: fractal dimension values
        (D-values), stability scores, lacunarity values, multi-scale profiles,
        geographic coordinates, camera metadata, and timestamps (collectively, "the
        Dataset"). The Dataset is accessible at
        <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Licence Grant</h2>
      <p>
        Subject to the terms and restrictions below, Fractune grants you a limited,
        non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable licence to access and use the
        Dataset for the following purposes:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Personal reference and education</strong> — exploring, studying, and learning from the data for non-commercial personal use.</li>
        <li><strong>Academic and scientific research</strong> — using the data in research projects, publications, and academic work, provided proper attribution is given.</li>
        <li><strong>Urban planning and architectural analysis</strong> — using the data to inform urban design, architectural assessment, and built-environment studies.</li>
        <li><strong>Journalism and public interest reporting</strong> — referencing or visualising the data in news articles, reports, and public interest publications.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>3. Attribution</h2>
      <p>
        When publishing research, analysis, visualisations, or reports based on data
        from the Fractune Dataset, you must credit the source as
        <strong>"Fractune (fractune.dk)"</strong> and, where applicable, cite the
        Dataset with a link to <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Restrictions</h2>
      <p>You may not:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Use the Dataset to build or operate a competing fractal analysis service or product.</li>
        <li>Bulk-scrape, mirror, or systematically download the Dataset through automated means.</li>
        <li>Use the Dataset to train artificial intelligence or machine learning models without prior written permission from Fractune.</li>
        <li>Sell, sublicence, or redistribute the raw Dataset as a standalone product or service.</li>
        <li>Attempt to identify, de-anonymise, or derive personal information about individual contributors.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>5. Research Partnerships</h2>
      <p>
        Academic institutions and research groups may request extended access to the
        Dataset for scientific purposes. Extended access may include bulk data exports,
        custom queries, and early access to new data fields. To discuss a research
        partnership, contact
        <a href="mailto:research@fractune.dk">research@fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The Dataset is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, whether express
        or implied. Fractune makes no representations or warranties regarding the
        accuracy, completeness, or reliability of the data. D-values are mathematical
        approximations derived from image analysis and may vary depending on conditions
        such as lighting, camera angle, and image resolution. You use the Dataset
        entirely at your own risk.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        This licence terminates automatically and immediately if you breach any of its
        terms. Upon termination, you must cease all use of the Dataset and destroy any
        copies in your possession. Fractune reserves the right to revoke access at its
        sole discretion.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about this licence, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:legal@fractune.dk">legal@fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .nav { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .nav-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    height: 52px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .nav-logo { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.375rem; }
  .nav-logo-icon { height: 1.0em; width: auto; vertical-align: middle; transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .page { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .page-inner { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .last-updated { color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  ol { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
</style>
